  "execution_target": "cpp",
  "optimization_notes": "Root cause: the prior plan used a logical path that reconstructs pure-row candidates from a uom posting index built on 32-bit words, forcing broad entry scans, rowid materialization, sorting, and expensive hash-map build/merge work before useful filtering. Strategy category A/C: reorder to filter sub.fy first, drive fact access through num_adsh_fk_hash postings for only relevant filings, and perform uom/value filtering plus (adsh,tag)->max aggregation on that reduced stream; this removes the heavy pure_rowids preprocessing and cuts wasted build work while preserving exact max-equality semantics.",
  "correctness_anchors": {}
